# Monorepo Best Practices (Turborepo / Nx)

## Repository Structure

```
monorepo/
├── apps/                   # Deployable applications
│   ├── web/                # Next.js / React frontend
│   ├── api/                # NestJS / Express backend
│   └── docs/               # Documentation site
├── packages/               # Shared, reusable packages
│   ├── ui/                 # Shared component library (shadcn/ui base)
│   ├── config/             # Shared configs (ESLint, TypeScript, Tailwind)
│   │   ├── eslint/
│   │   ├── typescript/
│   │   └── tailwind/
│   ├── types/              # Shared TypeScript types
│   └── utils/              # Shared utility functions
├── turbo.json              # or nx.json
├── package.json            # Root — workspaces definition
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml     # (if using pnpm)
```

### Naming Conventions
- Apps: `apps/<name>` — deployable, not imported by other packages
- Internal packages: `packages/<name>` — named with `@repo/<name>` or `@company/<name>`
- Never have an `app` import directly from another `app` — go through a shared `package`

