## Nx

### Key Concepts
- Use **`nx affected`** to run tasks only on projects affected by recent changes:
  ```bash
  nx affected:build --base=main --head=HEAD
  nx affected:test --base=main
  ```
- Define **project tags** in `project.json` to enforce dependency boundaries:
  ```json
  { "tags": ["scope:web", "type:app"] }
  ```
- Enforce boundaries with `@nx/eslint-plugin` rules in `.eslintrc`:
  ```json
  "@nx/enforce-module-boundaries": ["error", {
    "depConstraints": [
      { "sourceTag": "type:app", "onlyDependOnLibsWithTags": ["type:lib", "type:util"] },
      { "sourceTag": "scope:web", "onlyDependOnLibsWithTags": ["scope:web", "scope:shared"] }
    ]
  }]
  ```
- Use **Nx Cloud** for distributed task execution and remote caching

### `nx.json` Basics
```json
{
  "tasksRunnerOptions": {
    "default": {
      "runner": "nx/tasks-runners/default",
      "options": {
        "cacheableOperations": ["build", "test", "lint", "typecheck"]
      }
    }
  },
  "targetDefaults": {
    "build": { "dependsOn": ["^build"] },
    "test": { "dependsOn": ["^build"] }
  }
}
```

