## Shared Packages — Design Rules

- A shared package must have a **clear, single purpose** — no "utils dump" catch-all packages
- Every package exports through a **barrel index** (`index.ts`) — consumers import from `@repo/ui`, not from deep paths
- Packages must be **independently versioned** or version-locked at the root — decide one strategy and stick to it
- Shared packages must have their **own `tsconfig.json`** extending the root config
- Never have **circular dependencies** between packages — use `madge` or Nx's dependency graph to detect them
- Shared UI components must be **framework-agnostic** where possible (avoid Next.js-specific APIs in a shared `ui` package)

---

## TypeScript in a Monorepo

- Use a **root `tsconfig.base.json`** with common settings; each package extends it:
  ```json
  // packages/ui/tsconfig.json
  { "extends": "../../tsconfig.base.json", "compilerOptions": { "outDir": "dist" } }
  ```
- Use **TypeScript project references** for incremental builds across packages:
  ```json
  // apps/web/tsconfig.json
  { "references": [{ "path": "../../packages/ui" }] }
  ```
- Configure `paths` in `tsconfig.base.json` to resolve workspace packages without building:
  ```json
  { "paths": { "@repo/ui": ["packages/ui/src/index.ts"] } }
  ```

---

## ESLint & Prettier

- Maintain **one root ESLint config** that packages extend — never duplicate rules
- Use a shared `packages/config/eslint/` package:
  ```js
  // apps/web/.eslintrc.js
  module.exports = { extends: ["@repo/config/eslint/next"] };
  ```
- Run Prettier from the **root** — one `.prettierrc` for the entire monorepo
- Lint only **affected** packages in CI with `turbo run lint --filter=[HEAD^1]` or `nx affected:lint`

---

## Dependency Management

- Use **`pnpm` workspaces** (preferred) or `npm`/`yarn` workspaces
- Hoist shared dependencies to the **root `package.json`** where possible to avoid duplication
- Use `catalog:` (pnpm) or `workspace:*` to reference internal packages
- Run `pnpm dedupe` regularly to keep the lockfile clean
- Do not allow different major versions of the same package in different workspace packages — enforce with `syncpack`

---

## CI in a Monorepo

- Use **affected commands** to avoid running everything on every PR:
  ```yaml
  - run: pnpm turbo run build test lint --filter=[HEAD^1]
  # or Nx:
  - run: pnpm nx affected:build affected:test affected:lint --base=origin/main
  ```
- Enable **remote caching** — the single biggest CI speed improvement in a monorepo
- Run tests for all packages on merge to `main`; run only affected on PRs
- Build and push **only the Docker image(s) for affected apps**, not all apps on every commit

---

## Common Pitfalls

- ❌ Importing `../../` across package boundaries — always use the package name (`@repo/ui`)
- ❌ Circular dependencies — run `turbo run build` will fail; detect early with `madge`
- ❌ Forgetting `outputs` in `turbo.json` — cache hits won't restore built files
- ❌ Mixing internal and external package versions — use `workspace:*` for internal packages
- ❌ One giant `utils` package — split by domain or type
- ❌ No boundary enforcement — without rules, apps will start depending on each other
